Dialogue: 3,0:08:27.67,0:08:32.33,辉中 歌词,,0,0,110,,UPS: Unitized Pallet Structure 组合托盘结构
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.95,0:11:21.08,辉中 歌词,,0,0,110,,应该指的是TRAPPIST-1星系
Dialogue: 1,0:00:01.45,0:00:13.72,辉注,,0,0,0,,视频发布于2021年12月13日 发射日期以实际为准
Dialogue: 1,0:00:01.45,0:00:07.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,今年的12月21日 将可能改变人类对宇宙的认知
Dialogue: 2,0:00:01.45,0:00:07.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,This December, 21st may become known as the day the universe changed.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.72,0:00:13.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,在那个周三 NASA将要发射詹姆斯·韦伯太空望远镜(JWST)
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.72,0:00:13.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,That Wednesday, NASA expects to launch the James Webb Space Telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.72,0:00:17.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,人类至今单次发射过的最昂贵的航天器
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.72,0:00:17.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,The largest and most expensive instrument ever flown,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.88,0:00:22.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,比31岁高龄的哈勃望远镜强一百倍
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.88,0:00:22.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,100 times more powerful than the 31-year-old Hubble telescope,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.60,0:00:28.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST可以穿越时光 观察宇宙在创世之初的模样
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.60,0:00:28.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web can see back in time, all the way to the "let there be light" moment.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.74,0:00:34.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,那个又冷又黑的早期宇宙迸发出无数恒星的瞬间
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.74,0:00:34.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,That instant when a cold, dark universe ignited into stars.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.48,0:00:38.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,故事稍后开始
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.48,0:00:38.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,The story will continue in a moment.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.60,0:00:42.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,哇
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.60,0:00:42.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.81,0:00:48.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,比我想象中要大多了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.81,0:00:48.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,Well, somehow that's a lot bigger than I imagine.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:49.75,0:00:55.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,一年前 我们成为了少数在JWST上天前最后看了它一眼的人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:49.75,0:00:55.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,A year ago, we were among the last humans to see the telescope, much as it will appear in space.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.29,0:01:03.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,在我们此次来访后 它会被打包装箱 向月球之外的茫茫深空进发
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.29,0:01:03.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,After our visit, it was packed away for a journey of a million miles, far beyond the moon.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.14,0:01:06.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,永远留在绕日轨道上
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.14,0:01:06.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,To lie forever in the grasp of the sun.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.71,0:01:09.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,它能在太空运行多久？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.71,0:01:09.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,The operating life is how long?
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.63,0:01:13.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,设计寿命是5.5年 目标是10年
Dialogue: 2,0:01:09.63,0:01:13.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's designed for five and a half years, with a goal of ten years.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.85,0:01:20.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们要给它备足干粮 够它用十年的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.85,0:01:20.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,So that means we carry enough stuff on there to last for ten years.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.25,0:01:22.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,Amy Lo是一位系统工程师
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.25,0:01:22.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Amy Lo is a systems engineer,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.91,0:01:28.23,辉中,,0,0,0,,她带我们来到加州Rhodondo滩诺斯罗普·格鲁曼公司的无尘室内
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.91,0:01:28.23,辉英,,0,0,0,,who took us up in the clean room at Northrop Grumman in Rhodondo Beach, California.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.23,0:01:33.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们发明、设计、制造、纯手工组装
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.23,0:01:33.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,We had invent it, design it, build it, and hand put it together.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:33.38,0:01:38.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜底部的银色薄膜是它的遮阳伞
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.38,0:01:38.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of the spacecraft, that silver shroud is a parasol,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,有网球场那么大 为望远镜遮阳
Dialogue: 2,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,big as a tennis court to shield Web from the sun.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.74,0:01:49.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,而上面 是21英尺(6.5米)镀金主镜 面积是哈勃望远镜的六倍
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.74,0:01:49.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Above, there are 21-feet of gold-plated mirrors, 6 times bigger than Hubble's mirror,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.32,0:01:52.78,辉中,,0,0,0,,用来捕捉宇宙最早期的微弱星光
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.32,0:01:52.78,辉英,,0,0,0,,to catch the earliest starlight in creation.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:52.78,0:01:56.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,一共有18块六边形镜面
Dialogue: 2,0:01:52.78,0:01:56.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,There were 18 of these hexagonal mirrors.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.66,0:02:02.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,而当它展开后 它们会变成一整块镜子？
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.66,0:02:02.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,But when you fold them out, they all work in concert as one mirror?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.27,0:02:08.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,是的 18只眼睛会组合成一幅完美、高清的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.27,0:02:08.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,That's right, all 18 images will form one, very nice, solid image.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.18,0:02:11.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,而人眼并不能看到组合后的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.18,0:02:11.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,That image would be invisible to the human eye.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.89,0:02:17.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,类似于夜视相机 JWST设计是观测红外光的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.89,0:02:17.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,Like a night vision camera, Web is designed to see heat, infrared light.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.90,0:02:23.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为红外线是最早期宇宙留下的唯一痕迹
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.90,0:02:23.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because that's the only signature left from the stars at the edge of time.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.19,0:02:31.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,即便如此 那样的光亮还需要曝光几小时才能获得图像
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.19,0:02:31.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even that glow will be so dim, the mirrors will have to squint for hours to expose an image.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.07,0:02:33.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,您有多大信心？
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.07,0:02:33.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,How much confidence do you have?
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.01,0:02:37.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,呃……为各种事担忧就是我的责任
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.01,0:02:37.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,Errr … You know, My job is to worry.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:37.90,0:02:44.75,辉中,,0,0,0,,我个人还是比较有自信的 因为我们已经把能考虑的都考虑到了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:37.90,0:02:44.75,辉英,,0,0,0,,I personally feel confident that we have … thought of … everything.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.75,0:02:50.92,辉中,,0,0,0,,光是这个“考虑” 就花了25年 100亿美元
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.75,0:02:50.92,辉英,,0,0,0,,Thinking of everything took more than 25 years, and 10 billion dollars.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.92,0:02:54.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,工程师Amy Lo 向大家介绍了具体工程难点
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.92,0:02:54.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,Engineer Amy Lo, explained the challenge.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.15,0:02:59.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,我个人认为最大的工程难点是遮阳罩的部分
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.15,0:02:59.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,In my mind, the biggest engineering challenge was to build a sun shield,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.29,0:03:05.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,用来保护光学组件、镜面和望远镜仪器的遮阳罩
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.29,0:03:05.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,capable of shielding the optics, the mirrors and the instrument on Web.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:05.26,0:03:08.46,辉中,,0,0,0,,怎样才能把它造得又大又轻？
Dialogue: 2,0:03:05.26,0:03:08.46,辉英,,0,0,0,,How do you build something big but light weight?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:08.46,0:03:11.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,遮阳罩可以让JWST在暗处保持低温
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.46,0:03:11.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,The sun shield keeps Web cold and dark.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.19,0:03:16.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,来自太阳和地球的一丝热量都会影响望远镜的红外观测
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.19,0:03:16.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,Any infrared heat from the sun or earth would blind the telescope.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.56,0:03:22.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,五层遮阳罩薄如蝉翼 和生日宴会气球上的材料完全不同
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.56,0:03:22.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,The 5 layers are made of gossamer sheets, not unlike mylar birthday balloons.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.67,0:03:24.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,直面太阳照射的那层是第一层
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.67,0:03:24.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,The layer facing the sun is layer one.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.98,0:03:28.83,辉中,,0,0,0,,温度在230华氏度(110摄氏度)
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.98,0:03:28.83,辉英,,0,0,0,,And layer one reaches about 230°F.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.83,0:03:32.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,相当于个小烤箱了 煮个茶叶蛋没啥问题
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.83,0:03:32.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,So a pretty warm oven, like if you wanted to cook a morang or something.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.59,0:03:35.14,辉中,,0,0,0,,那望远镜那一侧呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.59,0:03:35.14,辉英,,0,0,0,,And on the … on the telescope side?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.14,0:03:40.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜那一侧 温度低至-370华氏度(-223摄氏度 50开)
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.14,0:03:40.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,On the telescope side, it gets to -370°F.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.48,0:03:43.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,两边温差有三百多摄氏度……
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.48,0:03:43.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's a roughly 600 degree difference …
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.97,0:03:46.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,-没错 -在遮阳罩的两侧？
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.97,0:03:46.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,-There is. -Between one side of the heat shield and the other?
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.53,0:03:51.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,是的 非常厉害 做到这一切 靠的只是这些……
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.53,0:03:51.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's amazing, that it's able to do this with nothing more …
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.99,0:03:53.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,这样的薄膜
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.99,0:03:53.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,than these layers.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.92,0:03:59.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜在工程学上已经很强了 但在科学上 它更是能够揭开宇宙的终极奥秘
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.92,0:03:59.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,The engineering is amazing, but the science may reveal the universe.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:00.10,0:04:07.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,自大爆炸以来 宇宙已经走过了近140亿年
Dialogue: 2,0:04:00.10,0:04:07.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,Since the beginning, the big Bang, the arrow of time has flown nearly 14 billion years.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.32,0:04:14.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST能够观测到最初一亿年——宇宙最早期的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.32,0:04:14.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web may see all the way back to the first 100 million, the baby universe.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.40,0:04:19.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,Amber Straughn是项目组里的天体物理学家
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.40,0:04:19.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,Amber Straughn is an astrophysicist on the project.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.04,0:04:24.99,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜就是我们的时光机 它能直接看到过去的事物
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.04,0:04:24.99,辉英,,0,0,0,,Telescopes really are time machines, they literally allow us to see into the past.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,原因很简单 因为光是有速度的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.99,0:04:29.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that is just due to the nature of how light travels.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.08,0:04:31.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,太阳发出的光要八分钟才能到地球
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.08,0:04:31.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,Light from the sun takes about eight minutes to get to the earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.96,0:04:35.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以我们眼中的太阳都是八分钟之前的太阳
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.96,0:04:35.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we're seeing the sun as it was eight minutes ago.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.02,0:04:38.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,放眼到整个宇宙 道理也是一样的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:35.02,0:04:38.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,And you can sort of think about stepping that further out into the universe.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.77,0:04:43.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以我们在夜里散步 仰望星空之时
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.77,0:04:43.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,So when we walk out under the stars and look above us,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.32,0:04:46.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,看到的都不是它们“现在”的样子
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.32,0:04:46.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're not seeing the stars as they are today.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.09,0:04:50.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,-我们看到的……可能是它们数百万年前的样子 -没错
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.09,0:04:50.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,-We're seeing them as they were, perhaps millions of years ago. -Absolutely.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:50.67,0:04:55.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,-因为光要花那么久才能到达地球 -是的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:50.67,0:04:55.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,-Because it took that long for the light to reach the earth. -Yes, for sure.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.33,0:04:58.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,人类对宇宙了解有多少？
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.33,0:04:58.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,How much do we know about the universe.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:58.95,0:05:03.76,辉中,,0,0,0,,从你我在这个星球上观测到的、我们对宇宙的了解
Dialogue: 2,0:04:58.95,0:05:03.76,辉英,,0,0,0,,Everything we know about, everything we can see, me and you, everything on the planet,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.76,0:05:10.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,观测到的上千亿个星系 只占整个宇宙的5%
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.76,0:05:10.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,all the hundreds of billions of other galaxies, all of that only makes up about 5% of the universe,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:10.65,0:05:15.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,剩余那95% 我们一无所知
Dialogue: 2,0:05:10.65,0:05:15.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,the rest of it, that other 95%, we have no idea what it is.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.12,0:05:20.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,那95%的未知事物 就像幽灵一样在宇宙中游荡
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.12,0:05:20.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,That 95%, the unknown, is all around us like a ghost.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:20.98,0:05:29.21,辉中,,0,0,0,,宇宙几乎都是由物理学家无奈称之为“暗物质”和“暗能量”的东西构成的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.98,0:05:29.21,辉英,,0,0,0,,Nearly all the cosmos is made up of what physicists call in desperation, dark matter and dark energy.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.21,0:05:33.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然从未观测到 但科学家推测它们一定是存在的
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.21,0:05:33.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,Never seen, scientists infer they must exist
Dialogue: 1,0:05:33.45,0:05:38.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为它们是星系构成与移动的最好解释
Dialogue: 2,0:05:33.45,0:05:38.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,because they're the best explanation for how galaxies form and move.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:38.96,0:05:43.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此我们认为暗物质是宇宙的一种“框架”
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.96,0:05:43.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,So we know that dark matter is sort of the scaffolding of the universe.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.80,0:05:47.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,它是星系所依托的结构
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.80,0:05:47.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's the the structure on which galaxies sit.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.28,0:05:51.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果没有暗物质 就不会有星系 更不会有我们
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.28,0:05:51.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Uh, and if there wasn't dark matter, there wouldn't be galaxies and there wouldn't be us.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.57,0:05:56.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST能揭示出关于暗物质的哪些内容？
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.57,0:05:56.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,What might the Web telescope reveal about dark matter?
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.12,0:06:01.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,就好像我们面前摆着宇宙140亿年的编年史 但却少了第一章一样
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.12,0:06:01.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's like we have this 14-billion-year-old story of the universe, but we're missing that first chapter.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.88,0:06:06.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,而JWST的设计就是让我们观测到
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.88,0:06:06.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Web was specifically designed to allow us to see
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.01,0:06:09.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,大爆炸后最初形成的那些星系
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.01,0:06:09.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,those very first galaxies that formed after the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:09.66,0:06:14.09,辉中,,0,0,0,,星系形成后 它们也会演变 会随着时间推移发生变化
Dialogue: 2,0:06:09.66,0:06:14.09,辉英,,0,0,0,,Now galaxies are born and then they evolve, they change over time.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:14.09,0:06:20.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,而星系的这种演变严重依赖于暗物质的存在
Dialogue: 2,0:06:14.09,0:06:20.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,And this way that galaxies change must rely critically on dark matter.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.28,0:06:26.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST可以让我们更清楚地观测到星系的演变过程
Dialogue: 2,0:06:20.28,0:06:26.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,And Web is going to allow us to observe that process of galaxy evolution in much more detail.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.60,0:06:32.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,载着全村人的希望 JWST的旅程一直都不顺利
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.60,0:06:32.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,The promise of discovery, shielded Web on what's already been a treacherous journey.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.62,0:06:38.79,辉中,,0,0,0,,它本来在七年前就该发射的 但却一鸽再鸽
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.62,0:06:38.79,辉英,,0,0,0,,It was to launch 7 years ago, but delays come with a machine this ambitious.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.79,0:06:45.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,由于成本超支 JWST在2011年被众议院拨款委员会取消
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.79,0:06:45.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because of cost overruns, Web was cancelled in 2011 by the House Appropriations Committee,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:45.31,0:06:47.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,但在参议院被保存了下来
Dialogue: 2,0:06:45.31,0:06:47.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it was saved in the Senate.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.66,0:06:55.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,它的名字 詹姆斯·韦伯 是60年代NASA的主管 让科学站上了首位
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.66,0:06:55.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Its namesake is James Webb, head of NASA in the 1960s, who made science at top priority.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.16,0:06:59.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,在JWST上你们都押上了什么？
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.16,0:06:59.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,What are the stakes? What's riding on that rocket with Web?
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.12,0:07:04.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,真要说赌注的话 就是NASA执行这个任务的声誉吧
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.12,0:07:04.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,When you talk about what's at stake, it really is NASA's reputation, to take on a mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.60,0:07:07.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,难度高 还没有失败的余地
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.60,0:07:07.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,That is as challenging as Web and be successful.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.87,0:07:10.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,Bill Oaks和Gregory Robinson负责该项目
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.87,0:07:10.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Bill Oaks and Gregory Robinson run the program.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:10.93,0:07:17.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,Oaks曾是哈勃的工程师 Robinson负责NASA的质量管理
Dialogue: 2,0:07:10.93,0:07:17.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,Oaks was an engineer on Hubble, Robinson has supervised NASA Quality and performance.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.22,0:07:22.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,真想在科学上拿出实打实的成果 就得让他们下血本掏钱
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.22,0:07:22.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,If you want to be bold and get the kind of science way after, you have to make them investment.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:22.67,0:07:26.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,而它也会解答两个大问题
Dialogue: 2,0:07:22.67,0:07:26.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,And it's going to answer two big questions, faster physics.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.31,0:07:28.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们从哪来 我们是孤独的吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:07:26.31,0:07:28.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,Where did we come from, and are we alone?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:28.50,0:07:30.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们很期待这些方面的答案
Dialogue: 2,0:07:28.50,0:07:30.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,We're looking forward to get those results.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.59,0:07:32.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST会成功吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.59,0:07:32.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,Is Web gonna work?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:32.29,0:07:36.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,-会的 我很有自信 -我有百分之百的信心
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.29,0:07:36.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,-Yes, it's gonna work, I have very high confidence. -I am 100% confident.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:36.26,0:07:38.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,百分之百？
Dialogue: 2,0:07:36.26,0:07:38.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,Why 100% confident?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.30,0:07:41.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,我看过了这些年他们做过的各种测试
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.30,0:07:41.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because when I look at the testing that we have done over the years.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:41.93,0:07:45.28,辉中,,0,0,0,,看到了他们在工程学上无所不用其极
Dialogue: 2,0:07:41.93,0:07:45.28,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the type of engineering that went into it,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:45.28,0:07:48.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,你就会慢慢感觉 这样的项目不成功天理难容
Dialogue: 2,0:07:45.28,0:07:48.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,you build a sense of confidence that you know what's going to work.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:48.57,0:07:51.06,辉中,,0,0,0,,您现在最担心哪个环节？
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.57,0:07:51.06,辉英,,0,0,0,,What are you most concerned about?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:51.06,0:07:53.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,整个望远镜展开的环节吧
Dialogue: 2,0:07:51.06,0:07:53.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Unfolding the entire telescope is what you worry about.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.93,0:08:01.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,望远镜需要折叠进阿丽亚娜5火箭只有16英尺(5.4米)宽的整流罩内
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.93,0:08:01.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,The observatory had to be folded into an Ariane 5 rocket, just 16-feet wide.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:01.18,0:08:04.04,辉中,,0,0,0,,它现在在里面就像花蕾一样
Dialogue: 2,0:08:01.18,0:08:04.04,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's wrapped today tight as a rosebud.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.04,0:08:08.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,发射以后 超过40套系统必须完美“绽放”
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.04,0:08:08.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,In flight, more than 40 systems must blossom with perfection.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:08.84,0:08:13.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括Amy Lo第一次制造的如此巨大的遮阳罩
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.84,0:08:13.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,Including Amy Lo's never invented before, Sun Shield.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:13.66,0:08:16.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,所有五层遮阳罩都要折叠起来
Dialogue: 2,0:08:13.66,0:08:16.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,All 5 layers will be folded up.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.98,0:08:20.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,然后用“图钉”固定起来？一共多少“图钉”啊？
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.98,0:08:20.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,And held in place by "pins"? How many "pins" are there?
Dialogue: 1,0:08:20.77,0:08:27.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,五层遮阳罩一共107个遮阳膜释放装置
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.77,0:08:27.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,There's 107 of these membrane released devices and "pins" that hold all 5 layers.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.67,0:08:32.33,辉中,,0,0,0,,把遮阳罩固定在这部分名为UPS的结构
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.67,0:08:32.33,辉英,,0,0,0,,Pin to this structure here, call the UPS, all Total 107.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.33,0:08:36.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,那在展开过程中 能允许多少个释放装置失效？
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.33,0:08:36.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,And, as you're unfolding, how many of those can fail?
Dialogue: 1,0:08:36.95,0:08:37.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,零
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.95,0:08:37.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,None.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.95,0:08:40.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,-零？ -零 -一个也不能坏？ -是的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.95,0:08:40.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,-None? -None -Not one? -Not one.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.00,0:08:42.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,完全没有出故障的余地
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.00,0:08:42.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is literally no room for error.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:43.26,0:08:48.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们进行了无数次测试与分析来保证
Dialogue: 2,0:08:43.26,0:08:48.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,We are test, and we do a lot of analysis to ensure
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.80,0:08:52.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,在太空每一个这样的释放装置都能正常运转
Dialogue: 2,0:08:48.80,0:08:52.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,that each and every single one of these will release on orbit.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.96,0:08:56.41,辉中,,0,0,0,,一百亿美元 就靠这107个“图钉”了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.96,0:08:56.41,辉英,,0,0,0,,10 billion dollars rides on those pins.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.41,0:09:01.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,哈勃望远镜在距地面340英里(550公里)的近地轨道上 拿个扳手上去就能修
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.41,0:09:01.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,The Hubble Telescope, 340 miles up, could be reached with a wrench.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:01.47,0:09:05.63,辉中,,0,0,0,,但JWST 在一百万英里外(150万公里左右) 谁也修不了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:01.47,0:09:05.63,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web, at a million miles, is beyond repair.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:06.02,0:09:11.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,Bill Oaks跟我们说 如果展开过程中有卡阻 那么还有一套紧急方案
Dialogue: 2,0:09:06.02,0:09:11.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Bill Oaks told us that if something does get stuck, there is an emergency plan.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:11.64,0:09:15.53,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们开发出一套控制算法让望远镜能……自行震动
Dialogue: 2,0:09:11.64,0:09:15.53,辉英,,0,0,0,,We've developed algorithms to essentially, may, we call it the shimmy,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.53,0:09:18.88,辉中,,0,0,0,,给望远镜引入一个小震动 让它前后摆动
Dialogue: 2,0:09:15.53,0:09:18.88,辉英,,0,0,0,,we do a little shake on a telescope and we can rock it back and forth.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:18.88,0:09:21.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,要是还不行 我们还能让它自传
Dialogue: 2,0:09:18.88,0:09:21.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,That doesn't work. We have one we call the "twirl",
Dialogue: 1,0:09:21.52,0:09:27.19,辉中,,0,0,0,,让望远镜原地顺时针逆时针转 看能不能把东西晃松开
Dialogue: 2,0:09:21.52,0:09:27.19,辉英,,0,0,0,,which can actually spin the telescope be the clockwise or counterclockwise, to help shake things loose.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:27.19,0:09:30.94,辉中,,0,0,0,,就像老百姓手里啥玩意不好使了就使劲晃晃？
Dialogue: 2,0:09:27.19,0:09:30.94,辉英,,0,0,0,,So you're gonna do what I do with devices when they're not working, you're going to shake it.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:30.94,0:09:34.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,对 对 差不多意思
Dialogue: 2,0:09:30.94,0:09:34.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, can I do the same thing? Yes.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:34.44,0:09:41.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,107个释放装置展开、镜面展开、其他上万个动作正常部署
Dialogue: 2,0:09:34.44,0:09:41.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,If 107 pins release, the mirror synchronize and 10000 things go right,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.47,0:09:47.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST携带的用于维持轨道与姿态的燃料也只够用十年
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.47,0:09:47.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web will be limited only by about ten years of fuel for pivoting and pointing.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:47.20,0:09:53.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,加拿大负责了望远镜的瞄准系统 能让它凝视宇宙深处
Dialogue: 2,0:09:47.20,0:09:53.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,Canada contributed the aiming system that will guide Web to wonders far and near.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:54.11,0:09:59.13,辉中,,0,0,0,,上千位天文学家都在争取望远镜的观测时间
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.11,0:09:59.13,辉英,,0,0,0,,More than a thousand astronomers around the world are competing for telescope time.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:59.13,0:10:02.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,Heidi Hamill获得了100小时的观测时间
Dialogue: 2,0:09:59.13,0:10:02.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,Heidi Hamill was granted one hundred hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.62,0:10:10.98,辉中,,0,0,0,,我有一肚子问题想问 我的专业方向主要在我们太阳系内
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.62,0:10:10.98,辉英,,0,0,0,,I have so many questions, my particular focus is objects in our solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:10.98,0:10:14.91,辉中,,0,0,0,,Hamill告诉大家 光其实充满了各种信息
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.98,0:10:14.91,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hamill told us that light is full of information.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:14.91,0:10:21.18,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST可以分析光的波长来判断存在的化学物质
Dialogue: 2,0:10:14.91,0:10:21.18,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web can define the chemistry of a place by analyzing its wavelengths of light.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.18,0:10:26.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,火星大气中的水含量是多少 它是如何随时间变化的？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.18,0:10:26.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,What is the atmospheric water content of Mars, and how does it change with time?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:26.62,0:10:32.26,辉中,,0,0,0,,是什么驱动了海王星上层大气的化学变化？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:26.62,0:10:32.26,辉英,,0,0,0,,What drives the chemistry in the upper atmosphere of Neptune?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:32.26,0:10:39.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们能否在木星或土星的卫星上发现水的存在？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:32.26,0:10:39.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,Can we see if there's water coming out of the moons of Jupiter or Saturn?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:39.05,0:10:42.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,无数问题我都想知道答案
Dialogue: 2,0:10:39.05,0:10:42.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are just infinite number of questions I want to answer.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:42.82,0:10:47.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,天体物理学家Natalie Batalha也争取到了观测时间
Dialogue: 2,0:10:42.82,0:10:47.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,Astrophysicist Natalie Batalha also has time on Web.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:47.35,0:10:51.29,辉中,,0,0,0,,她将关注太阳系外的行星
Dialogue: 2,0:10:47.35,0:10:51.29,辉英,,0,0,0,,She'll be looking at planets beyond our solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:51.29,0:10:56.48,辉中,,0,0,0,,平均下来 银河系里每个恒星都至少有一个行星
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.29,0:10:56.48,辉英,,0,0,0,,On average, every star in the galaxy has at least one planet.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.83,0:11:00.66,辉中,,0,0,0,,也就是说银河系里行星的数量比恒星还多
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.83,0:11:00.66,辉英,,0,0,0,,That means that there are more planets in the galaxy than there are stars.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.84,辉中,,0,0,0,,上千亿颗星球
Dialogue: 2,0:11:00.66,0:11:02.84,辉英,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of billions of planets.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:02.84,0:11:04.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,有了这么多行星
Dialogue: 2,0:11:02.84,0:11:04.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,And with that many planets,
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.47,0:11:11.36,辉中,,0,0,0,,Batalha相信JWST可以找到一些拥有适宜生命存在的化学物质与环境的星球
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.47,0:11:11.36,辉英,,0,0,0,,Batalha is sure Web could find some with the chemistry and conditions of life. 
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.36,0:11:17.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,恰好有那么一个恒星 有七颗行星围绕它运行
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.36,0:11:17.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,There happens to be one planetary system, the star has seven planets orbiting it.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:17.95,0:11:21.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这个恒星离我们只有40光年
Dialogue: 2,0:11:17.95,0:11:21.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,And the star is only about 40 light years away.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:21.08,0:11:27.31,辉中,,0,0,0,,是一个极好的研究目标 拥有三个地球大小的行星环绕
Dialogue: 2,0:11:21.08,0:11:27.31,辉英,,0,0,0,,So it's a great target to study, and it has three earth size planets orbiting
Dialogue: 1,0:11:27.31,0:11:32.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,而且这三颗行星都在适居带上 也就是可能存在生命的地方
Dialogue: 2,0:11:27.31,0:11:32.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,in what I would call the Goldilocks zone, where life could potentially exist.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:32.47,0:11:35.89,辉中,,0,0,0,,-不太冷也不太热 -没错
Dialogue: 2,0:11:32.47,0:11:35.89,辉英,,0,0,0,,-Not too hot, not too cold. -That's the idea, yes.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:35.89,0:11:41.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此它是我们要用JWST观察的第一批目标之一
Dialogue: 2,0:11:35.89,0:11:41.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,And so this is also one of the very first targets that we're going to observe, observe with Web.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:41.15,0:11:46.72,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们能够观测的是大气中的二氧化碳
Dialogue: 2,0:11:41.15,0:11:46.72,辉英,,0,0,0,,And what will be able to to see is … is their carbon dioxide in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:46.72,0:11:51.74,辉中,,0,0,0,,他们的温室气体是什么？是与甲烷结合在一起的二氧化碳吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:11:46.72,0:11:51.74,辉英,,0,0,0,,What are the greenhouse gases? Is their carbon dioxide in combination with methane?
Dialogue: 1,0:11:51.74,0:11:53.38,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为地球就是如此
Dialogue: 2,0:11:51.74,0:11:53.38,辉英,,0,0,0,,Because that's what earth has.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:53.38,0:11:57.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,因此通过观察这些化学成分 我们也许能够拼凑出一个结果
Dialogue: 2,0:11:53.38,0:11:57.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,So by looking at these chemical constituents, we might be able to piece together,
Dialogue: 1,0:11:57.90,0:12:03.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而了解到它到底只是一颗位于适居带的行星 还是拥有真正的宜居环境
Dialogue: 2,0:11:57.90,0:12:03.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,if it's not just a planet in what we call the habitable zone, but if it's truly a habitable environment.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:03.97,0:12:07.01,辉中,,0,0,0,,有人可能会问 这有什么好观测的？
Dialogue: 2,0:12:03.97,0:12:07.01,辉英,,0,0,0,,And somebody might ask, why does it matter?
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.18,0:12:11.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这的最终目的是想确认我们在宇宙中到底是不是孤独的
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.18,0:12:11.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,The end point is to … put an end to our cosmic loneliness.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:11.87,0:12:14.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们想知道到底有没有地外生命
Dialogue: 2,0:12:11.87,0:12:14.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,We want to know if there's life out there.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:14.33,0:12:21.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,您作为研究者的角度来看 JWST是创新还是革命性的望远镜
Dialogue: 2,0:12:14.33,0:12:21.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,From a researcher's perspective, is Web evolutionary, or revolutionary?
Dialogue: 1,0:12:21.98,0:12:26.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,每次你把一个全新的科技送入太空
Dialogue: 2,0:12:21.98,0:12:26.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Every time you put a new piece of technology into space,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:26.70,0:12:29.56,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者用不同的方法观测宇宙
Dialogue: 2,0:12:26.70,0:12:29.56,辉英,,0,0,0,,or you look at the universe with different eyes,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:29.56,0:12:35.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,都能有一些革命性的发现 一些从未预料的结果
Dialogue: 2,0:12:29.56,0:12:35.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,you … you learned something revolutionary, something that you couldn't have even predicted.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:35.05,0:12:37.59,辉中,,0,0,0,,我不知道未来会有什么惊喜等着我们
Dialogue: 2,0:12:35.05,0:12:37.59,辉英,,0,0,0,,I don't know what those surprises are going to be,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:37.59,0:12:43.08,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这些技术都是革命性的 所以一定会有革命性的结果等待我们去发掘
Dialogue: 2,0:12:37.59,0:12:43.08,辉英,,0,0,0,,but the technology is revolutionary, and there will be tremendous surprises that will astound us.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:43.59,0:12:48.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,JWST已经登上欧空局的火箭 就差临门一射了
Dialogue: 2,0:12:43.59,0:12:48.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,Web is on the doorstep, aboard a European Space Agency rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:48.97,0:12:51.39,辉中,,0,0,0,,包括Amy Lo在内的很多人
Dialogue: 2,0:12:48.97,0:12:51.39,辉英,,0,0,0,,Some, including Amy Lo,
Dialogue: 1,0:12:51.39,0:12:57.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,在望远镜长达一个月的部署过程中都会万分紧张的吧
Dialogue: 2,0:12:51.39,0:12:57.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,they hold their breath as it unfolds itself on the month-long journey to its station around the sun.
Dialogue: 1,0:12:58.12,0:13:01.17,辉中,,0,0,0,,大概六个来月后 第一张照片
Dialogue: 2,0:12:58.12,0:13:01.17,辉英,,0,0,0,,The first images, in six months or so,
Dialogue: 1,0:13:01.17,0:13:07.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,就会从红外波段转为可见的图片 登上头条
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.17,0:13:07.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,will be converted from invisible infrared into pictures suitable for headlines.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:07.61,0:13:14.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,可能只有到那时 我们才能真正理解这背后的奇迹吧
Dialogue: 2,0:13:07.61,0:13:14.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Chances are what we see, we will not understand the very definition of wonder.
